subject: PEL: Add error message registry entry for Panel
commitMessage:
PEL: Add error message registry entry for Panel

Adding error entry in the message registry JSON file for Panel code failure.This entry is used for any errors related to ibm panel execution.

Signed-off-by: Giridhari Krishna <gikrish1@in.ibm.com>
Change-Id: I9d6bdbde39ab556d8a756e38cf28f00d75cacb53

Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as c0cc7ec707ac95dcd784a103f4e3face6395e3ea
This needs a *lot* more detail.  Just one error type is not enough to cover all possible failures.
where did the internal error go ?
The standard is name them like A.Error.B, so like com.ibm.Panel.Error.I2CWriteFailure
I think we can call the subsystem just "panel"

it has to be valid subsystem enum in the schema which reflect the list of PEL subsystems.  Looks like there is a 'cec_op_panel': https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-logging/blob/master/extensions/openpower-pels/registry/schema/schema.json#L172
Can you claim 0x5000 as the component ID in https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-logging/blob/master/extensions/openpower-pels/registry/ComponentIDs.md put up a change in the same commit?
I2C writes to the panel failed, even post retries.
The Panel is unable to initialize the I2C responder. Butoon events will not be processed.
this should just be a set-up failure
this is. not needed ,we will have only one I2C setup failure error.
Yes, but we planned to have one for device path failure and ioctl, okay will differ in description then.

should we use 
"Name": "xyz.openbmc_project.Common.Device.Error.WriteFailure",
which is already available.
should this not be using the  "Subsystem": "cec_i2c",
@spinler: Any thoughts on this? Will using the cec_i2c subsystem give us any additional benefit?
There are other PELs that use cec_i2c on i2c fails so I guess it would be more consistent to use that.  Not sure if anyone would actually notice though.

do we need any of the below for our SRCs?
"Severity": "predictive",
"ActionFlags": [ "service_action", "report", "call_home" ],
"EventType": "env_normal",
These should be defaults if we have hardware callouts, Matt?

That's right:
Severity - we convert the Entry::Level severity to a PEL severity.  https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-logging/blob/master/extensions/openpower-pels/severity.cpp#L27.  It can't convert to every sev value of course, just the major ones, so if you need a different one you'd have to put it here.

ActionFlags - If not supplied here, we'll fill them in based on these rules:  https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-logging/blob/master/extensions/openpower-pels/README.md#action-flags-and-event-type-rules

EventType - we default to N/A if not informational, and misc/info only otherwise.
would we not want to capture the errno here ?
I guess if we reuse the Common write failure error, this will be taken care of too.
I'm not capturing that at present, will add that in panel code.
this is an input device open failure  not i2c
?? you just need to describe what this is , here you could mention that this is a failure in a PLDM send and likewise.

"Documentation": {
                "Description": "Dbus exception",
                "Message": "A Dbus internal error occurred.",
                "Notes": [
                    "This error occurs when Dbus operation fails.",
                    "Exceptions details are captured in additonal",
                    "data."
                ]
Might want to reword - We've added multiple entries, not justa  single
open/ioctl failure. Panel LCD may not work
peltool will display the Message field, so it would be nice if it were a bit more detailed here, even just copying the Description or Notes field.

On the first two errors, I suspect you'll be passing in the device information that the callout will be made from.

For this error, are you also passing in a callout?  If not, you'll want to specify one here.
This is a software error, so can you please suggest one. Should "bmc_code" procedure callout be good?
A minor formatting issue, else looks good.
This line is too long, please split into two.

DevPathFailure -> it can point to both
1. base and lcd panel's i2c device path (/dev/i2c-3 and /dev/i2c-7) and
2. machine specific input joystick path - ie.,button handler device path ("/dev/input/by-path/platform-1e78a400.i2c-bus-event-joystick")

Your description says this pel is meant only for button handler failure.

Which pel will be logged in case of panel's i2c device path failure?
can you change the PEL name to something like -> com.ibm.Panel.Error.InputDevPathFailure ?
